PRODUCT ANNOUNCEMENT

Latest Version 3.23 of MIRACL Multiprecision Integer and Rational Arithmetic
C Library now available via ftp. TEXed manual included. Now free for academic
& non-commercial use.

miracl.zip is available via anonymous ftp from ftp.compapp.dcu.ie
(136.206.11.247) in directory /pub/crypto (assuming Eamonn has set it
up properly....)

MIRACL is a portable C library. Full C/C++ source code included (In-line 
assembly support for 80x86 - very fast). Number theoretic primitives
needed to support PK Cryptography are supplied. Example programs implement
RSA, DSS etc.

C++ classes for Multiprecision Integers, Modular arithmetic, and Chinese
Remainder Thereom. Implementation in C/C++ of all modern methods of
Integer Factorisation, viz Brent-pollard, p-1, p+1, Elliptic Curve, MPQS

